<h1>Sudoku</h1>
<div id="board" class="board">
  <% 9.times do |row| %>
  <div class="row row-<%= row %>">
    <% @puzzle.row(row).to_a.each_with_index do |value,col| %>
    <div class="cell col-<%= col %> <%= value==0 ? '' : 'locked' %>" data-row="<%= row %>" data-col="<%= col %>" ><%= value==0 ? "" : value %></div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <% end %>
  <div class="available">
    <% (1..9).each do |val| %>
    <span class="value" data-val="<%= val %>"><%= val %></span>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <div class="controls">
    <div class="reset">Reset</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="instructions">
  <p>The goal of sudoku is to fill in all the cells.</p>
  <p>Each row, column and block must have the numbers 1-9 once.</p>
  <p style="font-size: .8em"><b>NB:</b> <i>'Easy'</i> Puzzles are more likely to be unsolvable.</p>
</div>